2
00:03:13.092 --> 00:03:16.084
<i>Cheers!</i>

3
00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:24.563
<i>Excellent.</i>

4
00:03:26.105 --> 00:03:27.868
<i>Let's drink 'till we drop.</i>

5
00:03:27.941 --> 00:03:29.704
Save energy for your wife.

6
00:03:29.842 --> 00:03:32.436
Are you kidding?

7
00:03:32.512 --> 00:03:35.276
Alcohol revives me.

8
00:03:35.348 --> 00:03:37.942
The later it gets. the hornier I get.

9
00:03:39.652 --> 00:03:42.951
Come on let's drink another glass.
A little sip.

10
00:03:45.291 --> 00:03:48.692
Tell me. Jane.
What college year are you in?

11
00:03:49.462 --> 00:03:52.192
- 4th year.
<i>- A senior should know better.</i>

12
00:03:52.398 --> 00:03:54.866
<i>What are you dolng with Tun?</i>

13
00:03:55.535 --> 00:03:57.264
<i>He's a hunk. huh?</i>

14
00:03:57.337 --> 00:03:59.771
You keep saying that
since we were in college.

15
00:03:59.839 --> 00:04:03.639
Making J im ask for girl's numbers.
Then breaking their hearts.

16
00:04:03.710 --> 00:04:06.679
Speaking of broken hearts.

17
00:04:06.746 --> 00:04:11.410
<i>Remember the time</i>
<i>that girl left him a drunken mess?</i>

18
00:04:11.484 --> 00:04:13.349
<i>Yes. her name was Kay.</i>

19
00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:15.654
Ignore them.

20
00:04:17.023 --> 00:04:19.184
Wait. I have a question.

21
00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:21.284
How can a guy like you get married?

22
00:04:21.361 --> 00:04:23.386
<i>What's wrong with me?</i>

23
00:04:23.463 --> 00:04:26.455
After a long. tiring day...

24
00:04:26.532 --> 00:04:30.969
I want to head home
to a wife's embrace or a pet's face.

25
00:04:31.037 --> 00:04:35.997
I can't waste my life
partying with you losers.

26
00:04:36.075 --> 00:04:37.474
<i>Well. not with me.</i>

27
00:04:37.543 --> 00:04:38.976
A good man...

28
00:04:39.045 --> 00:04:42.105
who went whoring with me
last night?

29
00:04:42.649 --> 00:04:44.947
Fooling around so soon?

30
00:04:45.952 --> 00:04:47.579
Here she comes.

31
00:04:50.123 --> 00:04:51.215
Quiet.

32
00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:53.088
Hello everyone.
What's so funny?

33
00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:54.491
Nothing.

34
00:04:54.794 --> 00:04:57.592
One last thing.
I want to tell you guys...

35
00:04:58.264 --> 00:04:59.822
One more glass!

36
00:05:00.633 --> 00:05:01.827
Cheers!

37
00:05:18.785 --> 00:05:20.548
What are we listening to?

38
00:05:22.689 --> 00:05:25.522
Why did you turn it off?
It's beautiful.

39
00:05:27.894 --> 00:05:30.021
<i>You guys seem close.</i>

40
00:05:30.196 --> 00:05:31.686
<i>Do you meet often?</i>

41
00:05:35.301 --> 00:05:36.996
Why're you staring at me?

42
00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:39.104
You're beautiful.

43
00:05:41.040 --> 00:05:42.405
What a sap.

44
00:06:24.350 --> 00:06:25.510
Are you hurt?

45
00:06:27.453 --> 00:06:28.613
Tun...

46
00:06:29.622 --> 00:06:30.680
Is she dead?

47
00:06:39.932 --> 00:06:40.694
Wait!

48
00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:51.104
Drive away.

49
00:06:52.678 --> 00:06:54.043
I said drive away!

50
00:06:55.515 --> 00:06:56.709
Jane! Drive away!

51
00:07:07.093 --> 00:07:08.822
Get closer. please.

52
00:07:09.695 --> 00:07:10.423
Okay.

53
00:07:11.197 --> 00:07:12.721
Big smile. Nuch.

54
00:07:13.466 --> 00:07:15.764
Or you won't look pretty.

55
00:07:23.810 --> 00:07:27.371
<i>All Science Majors.</i>
<i>Please gather for a class photo.</i>

56
00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:29.312
They're calling you.

57
00:07:29.715 --> 00:07:31.239
Where's Jane?

58
00:07:32.652 --> 00:07:35.553
Taking photos with her friends.

59
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:38.716
I thought maybe you broke up.

60
00:07:39.091 --> 00:07:41.082
Come! Let's go.

61
00:08:35.915 --> 00:08:39.817
I phoned but you didn't pick up.
Was it on silent?

62
00:08:39.886 --> 00:08:40.853
No.

63
00:08:48.628 --> 00:08:50.721
Nuch asked about you today.

64
00:08:53.966 --> 00:08:58.369
When will you be free?
Nuch wants to take you to...

65
00:09:18.991 --> 00:09:19.787
Jane.

66
00:09:21.661 --> 00:09:23.856
How can you act like this?

67
00:09:27.166 --> 00:09:29.794
Pretending like nothing happened.

68
00:09:31.270 --> 00:09:34.933
Since that night
I haven't slept soundly.

69
00:09:38.177 --> 00:09:41.010
You don't think I feel anything?

70
00:09:41.714 --> 00:09:44.911
At least we should have gotten off
the car and checked.

71
00:09:46.719 --> 00:09:48.710
It was an accident.

72
00:09:49.655 --> 00:09:52.453
That's easy for you to say.

73
00:09:52.792 --> 00:09:54.953
You weren't behind the wheel.

74
00:10:07.239 --> 00:10:08.729
- Hi. Ti.
- Hey.

75
00:10:09.008 --> 00:10:10.600
How's business?

76
00:10:11.043 --> 00:10:15.275
With you here this early.
my business's gonna be bad.

77
00:10:17.049 --> 00:10:18.778
Are my prints ready?

78
00:10:20.119 --> 00:10:21.950
Yeah. J ust a sec.

79
00:10:26.258 --> 00:10:27.088
Here.

80
00:10:50.816 --> 00:10:52.249
Is your processor broken?

81
00:10:53.352 --> 00:10:54.410
Let's see.

82
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:00.819
The nerve.

83
00:11:00.926 --> 00:11:02.826
If prints come out nicely.
then you're great.

84
00:11:02.895 --> 00:11:05.159
If they're suck. it's my fault.

85
00:11:05.564 --> 00:11:07.088
Check your negative.

86
00:11:08.034 --> 00:11:10.969
No way.
I took them. I knew they're good.

87
00:11:11.037 --> 00:11:12.436
Wait. We'll see.

88
00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:15.207
See.

89
00:11:16.142 --> 00:11:18.610
<i>Your negatives are bad.</i>

90
00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:42.059
Tun.

91
00:11:52.745 --> 00:11:53.541
Tun.

92
00:12:10.996 --> 00:12:12.327
Tun.

93
00:12:14.066 --> 00:12:15.761
Can you hear me?

94
00:14:18.991 --> 00:14:20.253
Help!

95
00:14:22.428 --> 00:14:23.656
Help me!

96
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:58.993
Don't be scared. I'm here now.

97
00:15:17.650 --> 00:15:19.777
What's wrong with your camera?

98
00:15:20.619 --> 00:15:24.350
I don't know.
The whole roll is ruined.

99
00:15:25.858 --> 00:15:28.383
That many?

100
00:15:33.532 --> 00:15:35.500
<i>What are these shadows?</i>

101
00:15:36.035 --> 00:15:38.299
<i>My camera must be broken.</i>

102
00:15:39.338 --> 00:15:41.966
<i>How should I tell Nuch?</i>

103
00:15:45.477 --> 00:15:46.444
Tun...

104
00:15:48.113 --> 00:15:49.910
Look at this picture.

105
00:16:00.859 --> 00:16:02.417
That woman...

106
00:16:02.995 --> 00:16:05.122
Do you think she's dead?

107
00:16:05.397 --> 00:16:07.058
That's enough. Jane.

108
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:14.940
I'll have my camera fixed tomorrow.

109
00:17:16.135 --> 00:17:18.763
Tun.
Look at this picture.

110
00:17:42.494 --> 00:17:44.359
Are you sure it was here?

111
00:17:51.103 --> 00:17:53.367
Excuse me.
What happened?

112
00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:57.368
A few days ago.
a car hit the billboard.

113
00:17:57.443 --> 00:17:59.934
<i>Must have been a drunk driver.</i>

114
00:18:01.046 --> 00:18:03.014
Was anyone hurt?

115
00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:05.406
No.

116
00:18:05.451 --> 00:18:07.009
<i>Just the broken sign.</i>

117
00:18:07.119 --> 00:18:08.177
Are you sure?

118
00:18:08.787 --> 00:18:09.719
What?

119
00:18:11.323 --> 00:18:12.881
Nothing.

120
00:18:13.659 --> 00:18:15.456
Thank you.

121
00:18:17.262 --> 00:18:18.286
What?

122
00:18:20.232 --> 00:18:23.065
You're sure
you checked everywhere?

123
00:18:25.904 --> 00:18:27.735
Nothing.

124
00:18:27.806 --> 00:18:30.400
Thanks anyway.

125
00:18:33.846 --> 00:18:37.782
My friend called every precinct
and hospital around here.

126
00:18:37.850 --> 00:18:41.479
No accidents were reported that night.

127
00:18:41.687 --> 00:18:44.087
That's not possible.

128
00:18:44.256 --> 00:18:46.451
What about the girl we hit?

129
00:18:47.926 --> 00:18:50.326
You sure he called every one?

130
00:18:50.395 --> 00:18:52.727
Maybe someone helped her.

131
00:18:52.798 --> 00:18:54.561
Maybe she's fine.

132
00:18:54.867 --> 00:18:59.133
How could she be fine?
We ploughed her down.

133
00:19:00.806 --> 00:19:03.297
<i>And even if she's fine...</i>

134
00:19:04.076 --> 00:19:06.340
Something is in those pictures.

135
00:19:06.411 --> 00:19:09.346
I've told you they've got
nothing to do with her.

136
00:19:09.414 --> 00:19:10.904
They're just bad exposures.

137
00:19:10.983 --> 00:19:12.211
Get it?

138
00:20:13.845 --> 00:20:15.244
Tun...

139
00:20:15.314 --> 00:20:18.249
You need to make some merit.

140
00:20:18.383 --> 00:20:22.615
These pictures show
that a spirit is haunting you.

141
00:20:29.194 --> 00:20:31.287
How long have you been
a photographer?

142
00:20:31.363 --> 00:20:32.921
Why are you showing me these?

143
00:20:33.165 --> 00:20:34.393
I know...

144
00:20:34.466 --> 00:20:37.697
But don't you find
these shadows strange?

145
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:40.902
You want to see spirits?

146
00:20:41.506 --> 00:20:43.235
I'll show you some.

147
00:20:50.649 --> 00:20:51.809
Here.

148
00:20:52.150 --> 00:20:53.708
Auntie Cham's spirit.

149
00:20:54.219 --> 00:20:56.119
You know where she is now?

150
00:20:58.757 --> 00:21:01.920
She's selling
grilled bananas next door.

151
00:21:02.628 --> 00:21:06.860
Here's Auntie Cham. And here.
All Auntie Cham.

152
00:21:06.999 --> 00:21:08.296
Taken on the same day.

153
00:21:08.367 --> 00:21:11.894
They're just double exposures
and out of focus.

154
00:21:12.337 --> 00:21:15.670
Come on. I know that.

155
00:21:23.282 --> 00:21:26.615
<i>Everyone is familiar with this place.</i>

156
00:21:26.685 --> 00:21:30.382
<i>Just an ordinary location...</i>

157
00:21:30.455 --> 00:21:32.548
<i>that we pass...</i>

158
00:21:32.624 --> 00:21:34.785
<i>and see everyday.</i>

159
00:21:38.563 --> 00:21:41.999
<i>Now look</i>
<i>at these following pictures.</i>

160
00:21:45.637 --> 00:21:49.038
<i>They were taken at the same place.</i>

161
00:21:49.107 --> 00:21:50.233
<i>In these...</i>

162
00:21:51.443 --> 00:21:53.604
<i>the bridge looks nicer.</i>

163
00:21:55.314 --> 00:22:01.617
<i>That means</i>
<i>photography does not reproduce reality.</i>

164
00:22:03.455 --> 00:22:05.889
It depends on...

165
00:22:05.957 --> 00:22:08.983
how the image is framed...

166
00:22:09.127 --> 00:22:13.188
what is revealed.
and what is concealed.

167
00:22:13.832 --> 00:22:16.824
<i>Your perspective is critical.</i>

168
00:22:27.813 --> 00:22:31.772
SPECIAL SCOOP: SPIRIT PICTURES

169
00:22:43.628 --> 00:22:45.186
Jane. you're early.

170
00:22:47.265 --> 00:22:48.892
I'll get it.

171
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:55.700
- Hello?
<i>- Hello. Tun.</i>

172
00:22:55.774 --> 00:22:58.368
<i>It's Jane. I'll come by later.</i>

173
00:22:59.177 --> 00:23:00.201
<i>Hello?</i>

174
00:23:00.278 --> 00:23:02.940
<i>Tun. can you hear me?</i>

175
00:23:03.081 --> 00:23:04.241
<i>Hello?</i>

176
00:23:04.316 --> 00:23:07.114
<i>Tun!</i>

177
00:23:07.185 --> 00:23:11.246
<i>Hello! Hello!</i>

178
00:23:37.716 --> 00:23:38.740
<i>What's wrong?</i>

179
00:23:39.518 --> 00:23:40.644
I don't know.

180
00:23:40.719 --> 00:23:43.187
My neck's hurt since the accident.

181
00:23:43.822 --> 00:23:45.881
You should go see a doctor.

182
00:23:47.259 --> 00:23:49.250
I'm sure it's not serious.

183
00:23:51.897 --> 00:23:54.695
What's the use of talking
to these spoofs?

184
00:23:55.667 --> 00:23:58.500
REAL GHOSTS MAGAZINE

185
00:24:00.572 --> 00:24:04.030
- Are you a reporter?
<i>- No.</i>

186
00:24:04.109 --> 00:24:07.135
The funeral foundation sent us.

187
00:24:09.047 --> 00:24:13.848
We run a legal operation here.
We have all the right permits.

188
00:25:00.732 --> 00:25:02.131
<i>Excuse me.</i>

189
00:25:02.200 --> 00:25:04.828
<i>Are all these pictures fakes?</i>

190
00:25:06.238 --> 00:25:09.605
Hey Piak!
Tell the boss he has guests.

191
00:25:11.276 --> 00:25:14.006
Everyone fakes them.

192
00:25:14.079 --> 00:25:18.311
You know
these photos are always a hit.

193
00:25:18.383 --> 00:25:21.318
Any issue with them sells out.

194
00:25:21.386 --> 00:25:25.379
Do you think
we can always find real ones?

195
00:25:26.525 --> 00:25:29.460
Isn't that deceiving the public?

196
00:25:30.629 --> 00:25:35.931
Our readers
pay to see scary photos.

197
00:25:36.001 --> 00:25:38.128
They didn't pay to read love stories.

198
00:25:39.304 --> 00:25:43.104
Does that mean every photo is fake?

199
00:25:46.177 --> 00:25:48.270
I didn't say that.

200
00:26:01.359 --> 00:26:02.417
Take a look.

201
00:26:03.295 --> 00:26:04.728
<i>See anything?</i>

202
00:26:05.330 --> 00:26:08.493
This is the first photo I had.

203
00:26:08.833 --> 00:26:10.960
<i>I took it In front of home.</i>

204
00:26:12.404 --> 00:26:16.704
<i>The shadow</i>
<i>bears a likeness to my mom.</i>

205
00:26:19.311 --> 00:26:21.677
Believe what you will.

206
00:26:23.148 --> 00:26:25.207
But this picture...

207
00:26:25.283 --> 00:26:28.116
was taken after she passed away.

208
00:26:29.888 --> 00:26:31.515
You know...

209
00:26:31.590 --> 00:26:35.788
sometimes
spirits long for their loved ones.

210
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:43.560
I n my opinion...

211
00:26:43.635 --> 00:26:50.939
these pictures represent
more than macabre urban legends.

212
00:26:52.410 --> 00:26:55.345
They are signs.

213
00:26:59.317 --> 00:27:01.808
<i>Think about it.</i>

214
00:27:01.886 --> 00:27:07.847
<i>Why would the dead</i>
<i>return to the living...</i>

215
00:27:09.127 --> 00:27:12.927
<i>without a message to convey?</i>

216
00:27:16.301 --> 00:27:18.565
<i>Most importantly...</i>

217
00:27:18.637 --> 00:27:20.969
<i>I belleve...</i>

218
00:27:21.039 --> 00:27:26.443
<i>these shadows are always</i>
<i>related to someone in the picture.</i>

219
00:27:29.948 --> 00:27:31.575
<i>A father...</i>

220
00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:32.844
<i>mother...</i>

221
00:27:32.917 --> 00:27:34.282
<i>iover...</i>

222
00:27:36.054 --> 00:27:40.753
<i>or someone you maligned in life.</i>

223
00:28:02.881 --> 00:28:07.079
How can we tell
if they're real or not?

224
00:28:07.552 --> 00:28:10.385
What about Polaroids?

225
00:28:13.858 --> 00:28:15.291
Can you fake them?

226
00:28:15.860 --> 00:28:18.328
<i>You load the film. press the shutter...</i>

227
00:28:18.396 --> 00:28:20.330
<i>and the photo ejects.</i>

228
00:28:37.882 --> 00:28:40.282
Tell me then...

229
00:28:40.351 --> 00:28:42.114
how can they be faked?

230
00:28:46.191 --> 00:28:49.183
How do we find out
what those spirits want?

231
00:28:49.260 --> 00:28:52.957
Perhaps
the answer is in the photo.

232
00:29:02.841 --> 00:29:04.399
Okay. last two poses.

233
00:29:05.543 --> 00:29:07.534
<i>Give me big smiles.</i>

234
00:29:10.381 --> 00:29:13.873
Let's have a different pose.

235
00:29:13.952 --> 00:29:20.152
Embrace her. hold the bouquet
and kiss her cheek.

236
00:29:21.426 --> 00:29:23.189
Very beautiful.

237
00:29:23.895 --> 00:29:26.295
That's it. We're done.

238
00:29:26.364 --> 00:29:29.162
Thank you both.

239
00:29:29.234 --> 00:29:32.101
Please take them to the dressing room.

240
00:29:57.061 --> 00:29:58.460
What the...

241
00:30:00.165 --> 00:30:01.723
Who's doing that?

242
00:30:01.833 --> 00:30:03.994
Aum. check the fuse!

243
00:30:05.236 --> 00:30:07.295
Hey! Aum!

244
00:30:10.608 --> 00:30:13.805
Who's doing that?

245
00:30:13.878 --> 00:30:16.870
Is it you. Aum?

246
00:30:22.453 --> 00:30:24.318
Who is it?

247
00:30:26.958 --> 00:30:28.391
Who's there!

248
00:30:29.594 --> 00:30:33.325
Answer me! Who is there?!

249
00:30:41.139 --> 00:30:43.073
Aum! Where are you?!

250
00:30:47.912 --> 00:30:49.209
Who's there?!

251
00:31:38.563 --> 00:31:40.326
Please step off the scale.

252
00:31:43.835 --> 00:31:46.030
Step on it again.

253
00:31:53.411 --> 00:31:55.242
<i>Been working hard lately?</i>

254
00:31:55.313 --> 00:31:56.974
<i>Not really.</i>

255
00:31:57.048 --> 00:31:59.482
<i>How long has it hurt?</i>

256
00:31:59.550 --> 00:32:04.681
<i>For quite a while.</i>
<i>But it's gotten worse lately.</i>

257
00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:06.781
<i>I had a car accident recently.</i>

258
00:32:06.858 --> 00:32:08.485
<i>An accident?</i>

259
00:32:08.660 --> 00:32:13.427
<i>Physically. you're fine.</i>
<i>You shouldn't be worried.</i>

260
00:32:13.965 --> 00:32:17.526
But I don't feel well.
It really hurts.

261
00:32:17.635 --> 00:32:21.969
<i>Your x-rays are normal.</i>
<i>It may be a muscle sprain.</i>

262
00:32:22.040 --> 00:32:24.770
<i>Try this medicine first.</i>

263
00:32:25.443 --> 00:32:28.344
<i>Mr. Tun. please pick up</i>
<i>your prescription.</i>

264
00:32:31.616 --> 00:32:34.847
<i>Take this medicine</i>
<i>3 times a day after meals...</i>

265
00:32:34.919 --> 00:32:38.286
until the prescription runs out.

266
00:32:39.991 --> 00:32:41.253
